<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871208-0021 </DOCNO><HL> TransTechnology Corp.</HL><DD> 12/08/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> TT BHWTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> LOS ANGELES  </DATELINE><TEXT>   TransTechnology Corp. said it purchased the assets of Bell andamp; Howell Co.'s Business Data Products division for about $10 million. TransTechnology is a maker of industrial and aerospace products. Bell andamp; Howell, based in Skokie, Ill., is involved in information storage and retrieval, visual communications systems and career education. </TEXT></DOC>